==General==

* English nouns are capitalised, this needs to be fixed.
* Tagger needs to be properly generated, currently there is
  only "de-en.prob".
* Punctuation needs to be modified to suit the German language.
  Examples of changes to be made (if not done already) are
  listed below:
	- Decimal places are shown by a comma (1.0 == 1,0)
	- Large numbers are separated by spaces or a period
		(20,000 == 20.000 OR 20 000)
	- Subordinate clauses are marked off from the rest of
		the sentence by the use of a comma (Als er nach
		Hause kam, war sie schon weg.)
	- German has a different quote system than English
* Numbers -- German numbers are joined, will need to use <j/> 
  unlike English with '-'.
* Is 'mit' a preposition or an adverb. At the moment it is
  categorised (as in English) -- as a preposition. This 
  should be investigated -- perhaps we should have two entries?
* Include support for verbs with separable prefixes:
	- anhaben -> to have on/to be wearing
		* Ich habe ... an. -> I have ... on.
	- anfangen -> to start/to begin
		* Es faengt um drei Uhr an. -> It begins at three o'clock.

==Test sentences==

Feel free to add test sentences. They can be tested with 'make test'.

===Basic===

We should be able to translate these perfectly.

#* Ich habe ein Bier.
#* Ich hatte ein Bier.
#* Ich habe die Hunde.
#* Ich hatte vier Kinder.
#* Du hattest vier Biere, und zwei Kinder.
#* Ich sah sie im Herbst.
#* Er hat ein Tier.
#* Ich bin ausgezeichnet.
#* Ihr habt Biere
#* Ich hatte einen guten Schiss
#* Spiele mit mir.

===Intermediate Complex===
Der Hund ist heute nicht hier, sondern morgen auch nicht.

===Complex===

These sentences are more complex, if we can translate them and get anything like the meaning, we're doing
very well.

